 {"id":"bd-31z","title":"Feature: Warm Model Daemon Architecture","description":"## Overview
Design and implement a **warm model daemon** that keeps embedding + reranker models resident for instant CPU inference. Eliminates cold-start latency for interactive CLI.

## Core Requirements
- UDS IPC with MessagePack
- Protocol versioning for forward compatibility
- Lazy-load models; keep warm with idle timeout
- Nice/ionice + bounded thread pool (rayon)
- Graceful fallback if daemon is unavailable

## Protocol (MessagePack)
Include a version field in every request/response:
```rust
struct Envelope<T> { version: u8, payload: T }
```

```rust
enum DaemonRequest {
  Embed { texts: Vec<String>, model: String },
  Rerank { query: String, documents: Vec<String>, model: String },
  Health,
  Shutdown,
  Stats,
}

enum DaemonResponse {
  Embeddings { vectors: Vec<Vec<f32>> },
  Reranked { scores: Vec<f32> },
  Health { uptime_secs: u64, requests_served: u64 },
  Error { message: String },
}
```

## Being Nice to the System
- `nice(10)` CPU priority
- `ionice -c3` idle I/O
- `setrlimit` memory + open files
- Rayon threads: `min(4, num_cpus/2)`
- Idle timeout unload + exit

## Phases
1. Daemon core (UDS, protocol)
2. Multi-model lazy loading
3. Resource management + monitoring
4. Client integration + fallback

## Validation & Tests
